Description: Angling away on a length outside off, Saha has a slash but misses. Porel doesn't collect that cleanly.
Full and straight on off and middle, defends it towards point off the front foot.
Oh pure timing! Length ball angling away, it was wide outside off. Saha stands tall and slaps it through cover-point. Not trying to hit it too hard.
And now Saha goes over mid-off! This is full and outside off, easy pickings. He clears his front leg and lofts it well over the fielder in the ring.
Full and outside off, driven straight to mid-off.

My word, has he struck it well!Length ball around off and middle, Saha picks the length early. Has it gone the distance? They are checking for that, looks to have cleared the ropes. Massive strike that, excellent start to the chase for Titans.
Gill is in SOME touch! That is on a length outside off, not too short, not too wide. Enough, though, for Gill to slap it through cover-point.
Lands it on a length around off, no movement off the deck or in the air. Gill defends it back.
Fullish around off and middle, keeps it out to the on side.
Beauty! And Gill is no beast. This is all timing. Length ball outside off, he stands tall and just places it to the left of short cover. Pure timing, all elegance.
Good comeback. Lands it on a length on the sixth-stump line, has Gill poking at it and getting beaten.
Angles it in on a length on middle and leg, tucks it to midwicket. Not a bad start from Mukesh.
Length ball outside off, he hangs back and punches it to deep cover.
Shortish around off, he hops and pushes it to backward point.
Length ball outside off, punched to cover.
Outside off, full as well, driven through cover-point for one.
Excellently played. Back of a length outside off, Vijay hangs back and swats it over deep midwicket. One bounce and into the ropes.
Full on middle and leg, pats it with soft hands towards long-on for one.
Nails the pull! Short and outside off, angling in. Vijay swivels and pulls it all along the ground through backward square leg.
Full and outside off, it is at 140.5 clicks. Vijay heaves it over cover for a couple.
Shortish on the stumps, he looks to pull but it lobs up off the pads to the on side.
Angles it on the pads, flicked through backward square leg for one.
Length ball outside off, he gets behind it and punches it through cover.
back of a length angling in, pulls it through square leg. He wanted a second but was sent back early.
Full on off and middle, nudges it through midwicket for a brace.

Just out of Porel's diving reach!Bangs it short, Sudharsan just looks to direct it to the on side. Gets a top edge towards short fine leg. Porel covers a lot of ground and puts in the dive but it was out of his reach.
Fullish around off and middle pushed to mid-off.
Fast and full length ball on off, he opens the face to get it through cover-point.
spears it full on off, perhaps he gets an inside edge onto his front leg. They rush through for one. Replay confirms the bat.
Length ball outside off, hangs back and slaps it to cover.
Back of a length outside off, he glides it to deep third.

Hugeeee appeal, the umpire stays unmoved again!Marsh cannot believe it and asks Warmer to review it. It is the slower one bowled full on middle and leg, Vijay is done in by the lack of pace and is early into his flick and misses the ball. Is hit what seems to be adjacent.The ball tracker confirms the same - three reds!The Arun Jaitley Stadium has just found its voice back.
Angles it in on a length on off and middle, he tucks it to fine leg.
Length ball outside off, he slaps it through cover. Mukesh slides and prevents the four, keeping them to two.
On the pads again, worked away through square leg.
Fullish and outside off, he goes for the drive and gets a thick outside edge to deep third.

Has Kuldeep got his man?The umpire think so and Miller reviews. It is flighted and lands it full around middle and leg. It is the googly, too. Miller plays for the traditional legbreak and misses it completely. Is it sliding down leg though? Only that can save Miller.Ball-tracker shows that it would have missed the stumps.
Flatter and quicker on leg, he goes back and works it away through midwicket.
Another googly on a length, Sudharsan doesn't really pick it well. Goes back to cut and chops it to the off side.
Lands it on a length and it is the traditional legbreak, goes back and tucks it through square leg.
Flatter on off, he goes back and slaps it through cover.
Shortish, he goes back and pulls it from outside off and through mid-on.
Bowls it full outside off, he clears the front leg an d smacks it to long-on.
Length ball outside off, he hangs back and slaps it through cover.
Low full toss on off, heaved away on the bounce to long-on.
Miller's arc and it is out of here!Back of a length outside off, he hangs back and heaves it well over deep midwicket.

Second six of the over and the ball boy puts it down!Full and outside off, Miller fetches it and heaves it well over the on side. Mid-on was in the ring and it was only about clearing him. He clears the boundary.
And this is hammered alright!Full and outside off, Miller gets the desired width. Thrashes it through covers to get the equation down to 26 off 24.
Length ball angling away, punched wide of mid-off.
Length ball outside off, he glides it to deep third.

Gets to a half-century in style! How impressive has B Sai Sudharsan been tonight. Back of a length just outside off, he hops and ramps it over the wicketkeeper. Almost went the distance. Jussssst bounces in front of the boundary cushion.
Full on off, worked away through mid-on.
Full and outside off, patted in front of point for a quick one.
Hugeeee! That is massive!Nortje bangs it in and angles it in. Sudharsan swivels and deposits well over fine leg. Batting exhibition.
Length ball outside off, chops it to backward point.
Pure timing from Miller. Full and outside off, he leans into it and hits it uppishly past cover. No stoipping that in the deep.
On middle and legm whipped to deep square leg.
Full on off and middle, flicked it through midwicket for a couple.
Full on leg, flicked away through square leg.
Full on middle and leg, clips it away through midwicket to keep strike.
Length ball around off, he works it away through forward square leg and sprints back for two toseal a six-wicket win!

Roaring start in IPL 2023 for Nortje!A 143 kph missile slanting in to Saha, cramps him for room and does him for pace. It is the nip-backer. Saha hops and looks to defend but gets beaten on the inside. The ball goes off his pads and disturbs the stumps. Titans lose their first.
Fullish and angling in, flicks it towards midwicket to get going.
Length ball in line of the stumps, defends it towards mid-on. Was a tad aerial.
Misses out on the full toss! !47.9kph on the stumps, pushes it straight and hares to the other end before mid-on gets around.
Full and around off, pushes it towards mid-on for a quick one.
Outside off on a length, punches it straight to covers.
Lands it on a length outside off, he looks to cut but it goes under the bat and on the bounce to the keeper.
Shot! Full and outside off, Sudharsan leans into it and nails the cover drive. Finds the gap between cover-point and covers.
Slower one around off,m on a length, he pats it to the on side and quickly gets to the other end. 114 clicks that.
Gill has missed out there. It was angled in on a length on the pads, he mishits his pull to short fine leg, Either side of that fielder and that would have been four.
Angles it in on a length, he works it away forward or square on the on side for one.
Fullish and outside off, driven to cover.

Jaffa! Nortje is well and truly making his presence in the IPL!It is a fireball at 148.8 kph. Gill, even in the excellent form that he is in, has no answer to that. It was speared in on a length around off, jags back in a touch. Gill was on the back foot and looks to defend but is beaten by the movement and is knocked over.
What a shot! Audacity at its very best. Fast and full at 144.2 kph on off. Sudharsan walks across and scoops it high and long over fine leg. Inventive strokeplay at its best.
Lands it shortish and angles it in, he tucks it towards square leg.
Banges in short and outside off, Sudharsan hops and looks to slash. It swerves in after it passes him and Porel fails to gather that.Given as runs but replays show that there was no edge.
Full and outside off, gets forward and drives it to mid-off.
Class!Overpitched outside off, it was the slower one at 121/6 kph. Hardik gets forward again and creams it through cover.
And he is greeted with a four! Full and on off, Sudharsan gets forward and flicks it through midwicket. No stopping that. 50 up for Titans.
Length ball outside off, glides it to backward point. Much better line and length that.
Peach! Cuts Sudharsan into two halves. Lands it on a length and has it nip back in. Beats him on the inside.
Back of a length outside off, he hangs back and steers it to backward point.
Length ball outside off, he hangs back and slaps it to sweeper cover.

And Khaleel gets the big fish Pandya!This is what Capitals wanted from Khaleel and he has delivered. Lands it on a length and gets it to come back in to off. Pandya is forced to play at that and pushes at it a touch. Ends up getting a thick outside edge and Porel has his first catch in IPL cricket.
Length ball outside off, he punches it through cover.
Bowls it on a length on the pads, he flicks it through backward square leg for one.
Full on off, driven straight down to long-on. The fielder was wider and that allows them two.
Full and outside off, driven through covers for two more.
Back of a length around off, he hangs back and opens the face to get it to point.
Full on middle and leg, flicked wide of midwicket for two. In fact, Rossouw misfields a touch.
Slider full on leg, flicks it towards midwicket for one.
Quicker and flatter around off, works it forward of square for one.
Flatter and turning in from a length, he goes back and works it through midwicket for one.

Excellent catch from Porel! Umpire is unmoved and Capitals opt for the review immediately. It is a googly on a length outside off, Sudharsan hangs back and cuts. It is too close to that but he goes with it. Seems to be an inside edge.Oh no, UltraEdge is as flat as it can be. Sudharsan seemed to be quite confident and he is vindicated. Capitals lose their review.
Shortish on a length, again a googly on off. He hangs back and pulls it through midwicket.
Fuller on middle, lunges and defends it towards cover.
Length ball on off, worked away towards square leg for one.
Full on the pads, worked away to fine leg.
Short and outside off, he hops and slaps it to sweeper cover.
Length ball outside off, stays a touch low. Adjusts and punches it to long-off.
All timing that. Length ball outside off, it is the slower one. Sudharsan hops and slaps it through covers to beat sweeper to his left.
Back of a length outside off, he lets it be.
Floats it fullish and outside off, it is the wrong one. Vijay plays inside the line and gets beaten on the outside.
Smacked it alright!Very full and outside off, it is the traditional legbreak. Vijay clears his front leg and hits it over the bowler's head.
Goes back, it is a touch short and low, hits it with the turn to deep square leg.
Lands it on a length on off, turns away. Sudharsan goes back and works it through midwicket.
Full on middle and leg, plays it with soft hands towards midwicket. Kuldeep himself gets to it and keeps it to one.
Full on middle and leg, pats it to the on side for a quick one.
